			]
			title: "Mana Relay"
			icon: "ars_nouveau:relay"
			description: [
				"В§fThe Relay is the 'wire' of your Source network вҖ” it carries magical"
				"В§fenergy from where it is generated to where it is consumed."
				""
				"В§eHow to link a Relay:В§r"
				"В§7  1. Hold your В§6Worn NotebookВ§7 and right-click the В§6SOURCE jarВ§7"
				"В§7     (the one that fills up вҖ” your generation point)."
				"В§7  2. Right-click the В§6Relay blockВ§7 you have placed between them."
				"В§7  3. Right-click the Relay block again, then right-click the В§6TARGET jarВ§7"
				"В§7     (the one your devices draw from вҖ” your consumption point)."
				"В§7  4. В§aBlue particlesВ§7 = linked and actively transferring Source."
				""
				"В§eRelay types:В§r"
				"В§7вҖў В§6RelayВ§7 вҖ” standard short-range transfer, small buffer (~500 Source)."
				"В§7вҖў В§6Relay DepositorВ§7 вҖ” pulls Source from nearby blocks into a jar."
				"В§7вҖў В§6Relay CollectorВ§7 вҖ” pulls from a linked jar into nearby blocks."
				""
				"В§eRange and chaining:В§r"
				"В§7вҖў Transfer range per Relay: approximately 16 blocks."
				"В§7вҖў Chain multiple Relays for longer distances."
				"В§7вҖў You can branch the chain: one generation jar can feed"
				"В§7  multiple Relays going to different consumption zones."
				""
				"В§eSmart base layout:В§r"
				"В§7  В§6Generation ZoneВ§7 (Archwood grove) вҶ’ Relay вҶ’ Relay"
				"В§7  вҶ’ splits to: В§6Glyph Workshop JarВ§7 + В§6Ritual Altar JarВ§7 + В§6Combat Reserve JarВ§7"
				""
				"В§7Name your Source Jars with an Anvil so you know which is"
				"В§7which when setting up Relay links ('Generator 1', 'Ritual Altar', etc.)."
				""
